name: Goenchin

reviews.review_text: Among the few restaurants running well for a very long time. And when you eat here, you know exactly why. The food is extremely tasty. Everything we tried was great. For drinks we had the goenchin delight and virgin mojito among others. The crab meat soup here is amazing and you gotta try it. For starters we tried the blackened chicken which was sooo good! A plate of chicken lollipops which were cooked to perfection and the spiced chicken with spinach was such a unique and interesting dish. Highly recommend all to try it. And the nasi goreng was epic! No gravy required and yet so tasty!
Our old time favorite go to place and we have never had a bad meal there. The food is consistently good. Would definitely recommend it.

One of the older Chinese food places in Panjim and owned by the same people who own The Mandovi hotel (now closed). The decor is decidedly 1960s. Service is fairly quick and the food decent. Prices are also very reasonable.

description:
**Goenchin: An Icon of Culinary Excellence in Goa Velha**

Nestled in the heart of Goa Velha, Goenchin is a beloved dining destination boasting a commendable rating of 4.3 from an impressive 1,143 reviews. Customers frequently highlight the restaurant's specialization in *Indian Chinese food*, underscoring its lush array of flavors that appeal to a broad audience. Signature dishes such as *crab meat soup*, *paneer dishes*, and *kimchi* have garnered significant praise, making them popular choices among frequent visitors. The consistent high quality of Goenchin's offerings contributes to its reputation as a culinary staple in the region.

**Ambiance & Design**

Step inside Goenchin, and you’ll find yourself transported to a time-honored space infused with nostalgic charm. The décor pays homage to the 1960s, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere that feels both casual and classic. Subdued lighting complements the retro aesthetics, making it a comfortable setting for family gatherings or casual outings with friends. The cozy interior captures a sense of familiarity that keeps customers coming back, as expressed in many reviews. 

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

The culinary experience at Goenchin is nothing short of delightful. Patrons rave about the distinct flavors and quality of the dishes. Must-try items include the *crab meat soup*, which has been described as "amazing"—a true standout, as one satisfied customer remarked. Other popular choices include the *blackened chicken* and *chicken lollipops*, which are cooked to perfection, showcasing the kitchen's expertise. The *nasi goreng*, a flavorful Indonesia-inspired fried rice dish, receives accolades for its depth of flavor without the need for gravy, emphasizing the restaurant’s ability to deliver satisfying meals crafted from fresh ingredients. The aesthetic presentation of the dishes, as illustrated by customer photos, enhances the anticipation of each culinary delight.

Dietary preferences are also accommodated, with a variety of vegetarian options prominently featuring paneer, catering to diverse tastes among diners.

**Customer Experience & Service**

Goenchin prides itself on quick and efficient service that doesn’t compromise on warmth. Staff friendliness is a common thread in customer feedback, with many noting how helpful and attentive the waitstaff is throughout their dining experience. The restaurant maintains a welcoming atmosphere, whether you opt for a reservation or decide to walk in. Many diners have noted that they have never encountered a bad meal, pointing to the restaurant’s reliability and commitment to quality service.

**Popularity & Reviews**

The buzz surrounding Goenchin is not just confined to its décor and food; the restaurant enjoys a loyal following that amplifies its popularity across social media platforms. Its reputation stems from years of consistent excellence, having withstood the test of time, as reflected in glowing reviews that celebrate both the culinary offerings and overall experience. As a legacy restaurant previously associated with The Mandovi hotel, its long-standing heritage certainly contributes to its allure.

**Utilizing Visual Content**

Images from thrilled patrons vividly capture both the inviting atmosphere and stunning food presentations. The well-decorated interior is evident in the posted photos, with bright colors and thoughtful arrangement creating a welcoming space. Photos of the *crab meat soup* and *chicken lollipops* highlight the thoughtful presentation and appetizing appeal of these dishes, making it difficult to resist trying every delicacy on the menu.

In conclusion, Goenchin is more than just a restaurant; it’s a cherished culinary institution in Goa Velha that has earned its accolades through a perfect blend of nostalgic ambiance, exquisite food, and exemplary service. Whether you're a local or a tourist, a visit to Goenchin promises an unforgettable dining experience steeped in flavor and warmth.
